To automate selecting all checkboxes and then saving them with a click of a button in JavaScript, you can follow these steps:

1. Select all checkboxes.
2. Check each checkbox.
3. Add an event listener to the save button to trigger the selection.

Here's a quick example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Checkbox Automation</title>
</head>
<body>
    <input type="checkbox" name="item" value="1"> Item 1<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="item" value="2"> Item 2<br>
    <input type="checkbox" name="item" value="3"> Item 3<br>
    <button id="saveButton">Save</button>

    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');
            const saveButton = document.getElementById('saveButton');

            saveButton.addEventListener('click', function() {
                checkboxes.forEach(checkbox => {
                    checkbox.checked = true;
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

This script selects all checkboxes on the page, and when the "Save" button is clicked, it checks all of them.

